Executive Profile
James G. Berges  Partner and Operating Partner, Clayton, Dubilier & Rice, Inc.AgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 6 Board Members in 6 different organizations across 14 different industries.See Board Relationships70--
Background

		Mr. James G. Berges, also known as Jim, has been a Partner and Operating Partner of Clayton, Dubilier & Rice, Inc., since 2006. Mr. Berges served as the President at Emerson Storage Solutions from 1999 to 2005. He was a Member of Emerson's Office of the Chief Executive, a Business Leader of Emerson Network Power and oversaw EGS Electrical Group. Over a period of 30 years, he held a number of senior executive positions at Emerson Electric Co. and served as its President ... from 1999 to November 1, 2005, where he led corporate growth and development activities including mergers and acquisitions, planning and technology and over the course of his career and was responsible for three of its businesses Motors and Appliance Components, Industrial Automation and Network Power. He joined Emerson in 1976 as a Director of Manufacturing Planning and has held key positions in its motor business, including President of Emerson Specialty Motors. He served as Group Vice President of Emerson since 1988 and as its Executive Vice President since 1989. He held engineering and management positions at General Electric Company. He serves as the Chairman of the Board of St. Louis Science Center's Board of Commissioners. He served as the Chairman of HD Supply Holdings, Inc from August 30, 2007 to March 2015. He served as the Chairman of Hussman International, Inc. from 2011 to 2016. He served as the Chairman of HD Supply, Inc. from August 2007 to March 2015. Mr. Berges served as the Non-Executive Chairman of Sally Beauty Holdings Inc. until August 27, 2012. He served as the Chairman of the National Association of Manufacturers. He serves as Vice Chairman at the U.S. Chamber of Commerce. He served as Vice Chairman of Emerson Electric Co. from April 1997 to November 1, 2005. He has been a Director of NCI Building Systems Inc. since October 20, 2009 and Atkore International Group Inc. since 2010. He has been a Director of Atkore International, Inc. since June 10, 2016. He serves as a Director of St. Louis Children's Hospital and St. Louis Regional Housing Alliance. He has been a Director of Atkore International Holdings Inc. since 2010. He serves on the Boards of National Association Systems and U.S. Chamber of Commerce. He has been an Independent Director of PPG Industries Inc. since October 19, 2000. Mr. Berges served as a Director of HD Supply Holdings, Inc. since August 2007 until November 20, 2015. He served as an Independent Lead Director of HD Supply Holdings, Inc and HD Supply, Inc since March 2015 until November 20, 2015. He served as a Director of HD Supply, Inc. since August 2007 until November 20, 2015. He served as a Director of MKS Instruments, Inc. from February 2002 to May 2007; Sally Beauty Holdings Inc. until August 27, 2012; Emerson Electric Co. from 1997 to November 1, 2005 and MCN Energy Group, Inc. since 1998. He served as a Director of Diversey Holdings, LLC and Diversey, Inc. from November 2009 to August 12, 2010. He serves as a Member of the Advisory Council at the University of Notre Dame College of Business. Mr. Berges holds a B.S. in Electrical Engineering from the University of Notre Dame.Read Full Background




